       o.meanra,
       o.meandec,
       o.ndet,

ORDER BY o.oid ASC;

-- Get AGN objects with high probability, long light curves, many detections, and significant variations
WITH agn_objects AS
  (SELECT o.oid
   FROM OBJECT o
   JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
   WHERE p.class_name = 'AGN'
     AND p.probability > 0.6
     AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
     AND p.ranking = 1
     AND o.deltajd >= 365 -- At least one year coverage

     AND o.ndet >= 20 -- At least 20 detections
), -- Get objects with significant magnitude variations in g and r bands
mag_variations AS
  (SELECT d.oid,
          MAX(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 1
                       AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
              END) - MIN(CASE
                             WHEN d.fid = 1
                                  AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
                         END) AS delta_mag_g,
          MAX(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 2
                       AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
              END) - MIN(CASE
                             WHEN d.fid = 2
                                  AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
                         END) AS delta_mag_r,
          MAX(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 1
                       AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
              END) AS max_mag_g,
          MIN(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 1
                       AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
              END) AS min_mag_g,
          MAX(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 2
                       AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
              END) AS max_mag_r,
          MIN(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 2
                       AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
              END) AS min_mag_r,
          COUNT(CASE
                    WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN 1
                END) AS ndet_g,
          COUNT(CASE
                    WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN 1
                END) AS ndet_r
   FROM detection d
   WHERE d.oid IN
       (SELECT oid
        FROM agn_objects)
     AND d.corrected = TRUE
   GROUP BY d.oid
   HAVING (MAX(CASE
                   WHEN d.fid = 1
                        AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
               END) - MIN(CASE
                              WHEN d.fid = 1
                                   AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
                          END) > 1.0)
   AND (MAX(CASE
                WHEN d.fid = 2
                     AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
            END) - MIN(CASE
                           WHEN d.fid = 2
                                AND d.corrected = TRUE THEN d.magpsf_corr
                       END) > 0.5)
   AND (COUNT(CASE
                  WHEN d.fid = 1 THEN 1
              END) >= 20
        OR COUNT(CASE
                     WHEN d.fid = 2 THEN 1
                 END) >= 20)) -- Final query to get all requested information

SELECT o.oid,
       f.name,
       f.value,
       f.version,
       f.fid AS feature_fid,
       o.meanra,
       o.meandec,
       o.ndet,
       mv.max_mag_g,
       mv.min_mag_g,
       mv.max_mag_r,
       mv.min_mag_r,
       mv.delta_mag_g AS delta_mag,
       mv.delta_mag_r AS delta_mag
FROM OBJECT o
JOIN mag_variations mv ON o.oid = mv.oid
JOIN feature f ON o.oid = f.oid
ORDER BY o.oid,
         f.name,
         f.fid;

comparison.sql_gold:
SELECT
    sq1.oid, sq1.ndet, sq1.firstmjd,
    sq1.probability as prob_stamp_bogus,
    sq2.probability as prob_lc_transient
FROM
(
SELECT
    object.oid, object.ndet, object.firstmjd,
    probability.class_name,
    probability.probability
FROM
    object INNER JOIN
    probability
    ON object.oid = probability.oid
WHERE
    ndet > 10
    AND classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
    AND class_name = 'bogus'
    AND probability > 0.7
    AND classifier_version = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
) AS sq1
INNER JOIN
(
SELECT
    *
FROM
    probability
WHERE
    classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_top'
    AND class_name = 'Transient'
    AND probability > 0.9
) AS sq2
ON sq1.oid = sq2.oid
ORDER BY sq1.oid
LIMIT 30
comparison.sql_pred:
-- Find ZTF objects that are likely bogus and transient
WITH bogus_objects AS
  (SELECT p.oid
   FROM probability p
   WHERE p.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
     AND p.classifier_version = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
     AND p.class_name = 'bogus'
     AND p.probability > 0.7),
     transient_objects AS
  (SELECT p.oid
   FROM probability p
   WHERE p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_top'
     AND p.class_name = 'Transient'
     AND p.probability > 0.9)
SELECT o.oid AS "ZTF identifier",
       o.ndet AS "number of detections",
       o.firstmjd AS "first detection date",
       p_bogus.probability AS prob_stamp_bogus,
       p_transient.probability AS prob_lc_transient
FROM OBJECT o
JOIN bogus_objects bo ON o.oid = bo.oid
JOIN transient_objects to_obj ON o.oid = to_obj.oid
JOIN probability p_bogus ON o.oid = p_bogus.oid
AND p_bogus.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier'
AND p_bogus.classifier_version = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
AND p_bogus.class_name = 'bogus'
JOIN probability p_transient ON o.oid = p_transient.oid
AND p_transient.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier_top'
AND p_transient.class_name = 'Transient'
WHERE o.ndet > 10
ORDER BY o.oid
LIMIT 30;

  sq.oid, sq.meanra, sq.meandec,
  detection.candid, detection.fid as f_id,detection.magpsf, detection.sigmapsf_corr, detection.sigmapsf_corr_ext
FROM
  (
SELECT
    object.oid, object.meanra, object.meandec, object.ndet
FROM
    object INNER JOIN
    probability
    ON object.oid = probability.oid
WHERE
    probability.classifier_name='lc_classifier_stochastic'
    AND probability.class_name='CV/Nova'
    AND probability.ranking = 1
) AS sq
  INNER JOIN detection
  ON sq.oid = detection.oid
WHERE
  sq.ndet < 50
  AND detection.fid = 2
ORDER BY oid
LIMIT 1000

ORDER BY d.oid
LIMIT 1000;
